text: Raphael Bouju (born 15 May 2002) is a Dutch sprinter. Bouju represents the Netherlands at international competitions. He became under-18 European champion in the 100 metres at the 2018 European Athletics U18 Championships. Bouju became 2022 national champion in the 100 metres. After the national championships he competed at the 2022 World Athletics Championships in the 4 × 100 metres relay event. He competed at the 2022 European Athletics Championships in the 4 × 100 metres relay event finishing in fourth place. ==References== Category:2002 births Category:Dutch sprinters Category:Living people
